  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Accounting & HR Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Accounting & Finance</strong></p><ul><li>Manage <strong>full set of accounts</strong> (AP, AR, GL, bank reconciliation)</li><li>Prepare <strong>monthly financial statements, management reports, and budgets.</strong></li><li>Ensure compliance with <strong>accounting standards, tax regulations, and statutory requirements</strong></li><li>Handle <strong>cash flow management</strong>, invoicing, and payments.</li><li>Maintain proper <strong>financial records and internal controls.</strong></li><li>Oversee <strong>invoicing, collections, and credit control</strong></li><li>Ensure timely processing of <strong>supplier invoices and payments</strong></li><li>Monitor aging reports and follow up on overdue receivables3</li><li>Liaise with <strong>auditors, tax agents, banks, and authorities</strong></li><li>Coordinate <strong>internal and external audits</strong></li><li>Maintain and improve <strong>internal control systems and accounting procedures</strong></li><li>Address audit findings and implement corrective actions</li><li>Ensure compliance with <strong>local accounting standards (IFRS/GAAP)</strong></li><li>Handle <strong>GST/VAT submissions</strong>, corporate tax filings, and withholding tax</li><li>Coordinate with <strong>tax agents and auditors</strong> for statutory submissions</li><li>Ensure timely compliance with regulatory and statutory requirements</li></ul><p><strong>Human Resources</strong></p><p><ul><li>Manage <strong>end-to-end HR operations</strong> including recruitment, onboarding, and offboarding.</li><li>Handle <strong>payroll processing</strong>, CPF submissions, and employee benefits.</li><li>Administer <strong>leave, attendance, and HR records</strong>.</li><li>Ensure compliance with <strong>local employment laws and MOM regulations</strong></li><li>Support performance appraisal and staff development processes.</li><li>Others duties might be assigned by company or head of Finance & HR</li></ul></p>",
